## Stack
- API: Hono on Cloudflare Workers
{{#if db}}
- ORM: Drizzle with D1
{{/if}}
{{#if auth}}
- Auth: Better Auth (self-hosted, D1-backed)
{{/if}}
- Web: Vite + React
- Language: TypeScript
- Package manager: pnpm
- Linting: Biome
{{#if e2e}}
- E2E Testing: Playwright
{{/if}}
- Unit Testing: Vitest (only for pure logic)

## Commands
- `pnpm dev` - start API dev server (wrangler)
- `pnpm dev:web` - start web frontend dev server (vite)
- `pnpm lint` - check formatting and lint
- `pnpm lint:fix` - auto-fix lint issues
- `pnpm typecheck` - TypeScript type checking
- `pnpm test` - run unit tests (vitest)
{{#if e2e}}
- `pnpm test:e2e` - run full Playwright E2E suite
- `pnpm test:e2e:smoke` - run smoke tests only (@smoke tag)
- `pnpm test:e2e:ui` - run E2E tests with Playwright UI
{{/if}}
{{#if db}}
- `pnpm db:generate` - generate DB migration
- `pnpm db:migrate` - run DB migrations
{{/if}}

## Structure
- `src/app/` - API routes, handlers, services, schemas (platform-agnostic, pure Hono)
- `src/platform/` - Cloudflare adapter (thin layer, only place for Workers-specific code)
{{#if db}}
- `src/db/` - Drizzle schema and migrations
{{/if}}
{{#if auth}}
- `src/auth/` - Better Auth config and Hono middleware
{{/if}}
- `src/lib/` - Shared utilities
- `src/workers/` - Queue consumers, cron handlers
- `src/web/` - Frontend (Vite + React)
{{#if e2e}}
- `e2e/` - Playwright E2E tests (smoke.spec.ts for critical paths)
{{/if}}
- `tests/` - Unit tests (only for pure algorithmic logic)

## Architecture: Platform Separation
Routes and business logic must be platform-agnostic:
- `src/app/routes/` and `src/app/services/` — pure Hono, NO Cloudflare imports, no direct `env.DB` access
- `src/platform/cloudflare.ts` — thin adapter, the ONLY place that touches Workers-specific APIs
{{#if db}}
- If a migration or query uses something specific to D1/SQLite that wouldn't work on Postgres, ask first
{{/if}}

## Testing Strategy
- Do NOT write unit tests by default. Only for pure algorithmic/business logic with clear inputs/outputs.
{{#if e2e}}
- Write Playwright E2E tests for user-facing flows.
- Tag critical path tests with `@smoke` in the test.describe name — these run in CI on merge.
- Full E2E suite runs locally, not in CI.
{{/if}}
- When writing tests, define the scenarios clearly. Test what the user sees, not implementation details.

## Rules

### Code Quality
- Run `pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck` before claiming anything is done
- Use path aliases (`@/`) instead of deep relative imports
- Keep the dev server startable with one command

### No Silent Failures
- NEVER add empty catch blocks or swallow errors
- NEVER add defensive defaults that make code pass instead of failing when there's a bug
- NEVER add backward-compatibility shims or fallbacks without asking — this may be v0, breaking changes are fine
- Let errors propagate and crash loudly. If something fails, it should fail visibly.
- If tempted to add a try/catch or default value to make code "work", ask whether the failure should be surfaced instead

### Boundaries
- Do not switch package managers or add major dependencies without asking
- Keep PRs focused on one thing
- Do not modify CI workflows or deploy configs without explicit approval
{{#if db}}
- Do not change DB schema without generating and reviewing a migration
{{/if}}
- When stuck, say so — do not silently guess and ship broken code
